    <div class="section">
      

<div id="review_13043902" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/13043902" />
    <a title="Jenifer" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/809099-jenifer"><img alt="Jenifer" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1200930531p2/809099.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/13043902?book_show_action=true">Jan 21, 2008</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Jenifer" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Jenifer" href="/user/show/809099-jenifer">Jenifer</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>



        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer13043902" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer3224024354767828094">Christopher Hitchens, why so angry? This is an interesting collection of essays, fiction, articles and arguments, compiled by the acidic and immature Hitchens. When Hitchens is NOT speaking, this proves evocative reading. When he is, it&apos;s annoying - like listening to a teenage girl on a cell phone on the train fighting with her boyfriend-of-the-week about &quot;I know you are, but what am I? Shut up no you shut up you stupidhead meanyperson.&quot; </span>
  <span id="freeText3224024354767828094" style="display:none">Christopher Hitchens, why so angry? This is an interesting collection of essays, fiction, articles and arguments, compiled by the acidic and immature Hitchens. When Hitchens is NOT speaking, this proves evocative reading. When he is, it's annoying - like listening to a teenage girl on a cell phone on the train fighting with her boyfriend-of-the-week about "I know you are, but what am I? Shut up no you shut up you stupidhead meanyperson." </span>
