<span id="freeTextContainer10747617766929211349">Some thoughts from reading snippets of this tome for my job . . .<br/><br/>1. At 500 pages and a few pounds, this is anything but &quot;portable&quot;<br/>2. For people who don&apos;t believe in a God, they spend an awful lot of time and energy talking about Him.<br/>3. If this is a true representation of atheists, then they are egotistical, arrogant, vile, cruel, hate-filled, and generally depressive people.</span>
  <span id="freeText10747617766929211349" style="display:none">Some thoughts from reading snippets of this tome for my job . . .<br /><br />1. At 500 pages and a few pounds, this is anything but "portable"<br />2. For people who don't believe in a God, they spend an awful lot of time and energy talking about Him.<br />3. If this is a true representation of atheists, then they are egotistical, arrogant, vile, cruel, hate-filled, and generally depressive people.</span>
